-labels`, `data-y-labels`, `data-x-labels-vertical`, `data-x-baseline`, `data-y-baseline`, `data-x-tick-marks`, `data-y-tick-marks`"},"1441":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-73","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#component-customization","content":"Use the `className` prop on the chart container to add or override styles:"},"1442":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-74","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Provide &#x2A;*`aria-label`** to describe the chart (e.g. \"Monthly sales revenue from January to May 2024\")."},"1443":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-75","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Use &#x2A;*`desc`** for a longer description rendered in the SVG `<desc>` for screen readers."},"1444":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-76","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"The component sets ARIA attributes on interactive and structural elements as needed."},"1445":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-77","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#chart-not-sizing-or-empty","content":"Ensure the chart has a non-zero size. Place it in a container with explicit dimensions or use `width` and `height`:"},"1446":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-78","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#dates-not-displaying-correctly","content":"Use `xType=\"time\"` when the X-axis values are Date objects:"},"1447":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-79","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#tooltip-or-crosshair-not-showing","content":"Ensure `tooltip`, `showCrosshair`, or `showDataPoints` are not set to `false`, and that the chart receives pointer events (e.g. no overlay blocking hover)."},"1448":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-80","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use for trends over time or along a continuous scale."},"1449":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-81","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use when comparing a few series (e.g. 2–5 lines); avoid too many overlapping lines."},"1450":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-82","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Prefer a single chart with a legend over multiple small charts when comparing the same X range."},"1451":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"page","content":"DonutChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart"},"1452":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","content":"Donut charts are for parts-to-whole comparison—how partial elements add up to a total—shown as a ring so a few categories are easy to compare at a glance."},"1453":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#installation","content":"Installation"},"1454":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#props","content":"Props"},"1455":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1456":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"Basic"},"1457":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"Single slice"},"1458":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Legend placement"},"1459":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Small slices"},"1460":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Format value"},"1461":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-9","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#basic","content":"You give the chart a `data` array (`id`, `name`, `value`) and a `label` in the middle—this is the everyday setup when you want several categories on one ring and a headline number or title in the hole."},"1462":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#single-slice","content":"When there is only one slice, the ring is full. Add `subLabel` if you want a smaller second line under the main center text."},"1463":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#legend-placement","content":"Switch `legend` to `right` to sit the legend beside the donut, or `bottom` to stack it underneath. `legendLabel` is there when you want a title above the legend items."},"1464":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#small-slices","content":"Very thin slices can be noisy to hover. Anything at or below `smallSliceThreshold` (default `0.05` of the total) is treated as “small,” and if those slices sit next to each other on the ring, one hover opens a single tooltip that lists the whole group."},"1465":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/donut-chart#format-value","content":"Use `formatValue` when the raw numbers in the tooltip should read like money, counts with separators, or whatever your product expects. The percentage of the total still formats on its own; your function only shapes the value column."},"1466":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"page","content":"Box","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box"},"1467":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Polymorphic layout component providing consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment"},"1468":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#installation","content":"Installation"},"1469":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#pro